totalDeathsBoxplotHeaderHTML.html: How to interpret these charts: The bar across the middle of the box gives the median of all states on that date. Half the states fall within the box, a quarter above it and a quarter below it. Dots in a horizontal line near the top of the graph are not real data, but mean there is a data point at that level or higher (if the graph were scaled to show everything, the interesting part of the graph would be all squished at the bottom)
